                     java.lang.String lastsync,
                     java.lang.String storetype,
                     java.lang.String googleConnectorWorkDir)
Default Constructor for the connector called only by the spring framework onstartup of the connector itself. This class isn't designed to be instantiated by itself manually.

When the system starts up, the parameters defined in the connectorInstance.xml is used inorder to call this connector

The login_session hashmap storing the authenticated sessions is also initialized

Documentation about the quartz scheduler: http://www.opensymphony.com/quartz/wikidocs/CronTriggers%20Tutorial.html

The Query terms wildcards right now is $LAST_SYNC_DATE. THis wildcard, if found in the query parmaeter, is substituted with the last time the quartz scheduler ran.

Parameters:
username - The username the connector should use to login as
password - the login password
schedule - the CRON schedule
query - used to get the salesforce data per iteration
xslt - used to transform the query response into the connector feed and HTML cache copy. This param must be BASE64 ENCODED
azquery - the authentication query to see if a user is allowed to even get on salesforce
azxslt - the xslt to transform the authentiation query back into a canonical xml form the connector can process. This param must be BASE64 ENCODED
loginsrv - the login server the connector should use
lastsync - the last time the Connector's Quartz scheduler ran completely
storetype - the last time the Connector's Quartz scheduler ran completely
googleConnectorWorkDir - the working directory for this connector WEB-INF/connectors/salesforce-connector/

Sets the user session for the authenticated user has with salesforce during a secure search

This routine also specifies if the user had a STRONG_AUTHENTICATION (complete login) or a WEAK Authentication (partial/inferred login)

Parameters:
username - from AuthenticationIdentity.id
login_server - the login server this authenticated user should use
sessionID - for the user in context
auth_type - type used
